id: pm-qtbc
title: "pm-mcp bin is dead on npm installs: main-module guard fails under symlinked argv[1] (silent exit 0, no JSON-RPC output)"
description: "Repro: printf '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"initialize\",\"params\":{\"protocolVersion\":\"2025-06-18\",\"capabilities\":{},\"clientInfo\":{\"name\":\"x\",\"version\":\"1\"}}}\\n' | pm-mcp -> exit 0, EMPTY stdout/stderr. Same request piped to 'node dist/mcp/server.js' responds correctly (serverInfo 2026.6.12, 25 tools). Cause: src/mcp/server.ts:1173 'if (process.argv[1] && fileURLToPath(import.meta.url) === process.argv[1])' — npm bin entries are SYMLINKS (e.g. ~/.local/share/mise/installs/node/25.9.0/bin/pm-mcp -> ../lib/node_modules/@unbrained/pm-cli/dist/mcp/server.js); Node resolves import.meta.url to the realpath while argv[1] keeps the symlink path, so the guard never matches and the process exits 0 without serving. Minimal repro: ln -s dist/mcp/server.js /tmp/x && node /tmp/x -> no output. Fix: compare via fs.realpathSync(process.argv[1]) (wrapped in try/catch), e.g. realpath both sides before comparing. Affects every npm global/local install of the pm-mcp binary on Linux/macOS; silent exit 0 is the worst failure mode for MCP clients (looks like instant clean shutdown)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: bug,dogfood-2026-06-12,mcp
created_at: "2026-06-12T16:18:28.696Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T16:56:01.081Z"
author: maintainer-agent
resolution: Fixed pm-mcp main-module detection by realpath-resolving symlinked npm bin argv paths.
expected_result: npm-style symlinked pm-mcp starts the MCP stdio server and responds to initialize.
actual_result: Integration and manual symlink smoke both returned serverInfo.name=pm-mcp.
